Question

Match the following equations to their graphs.

  1. \(y=- \frac{\left(x - 2\right) \left(x + 2\right)}{2}\)
  2. \(y=\frac{\left(x - 5\right) \left(x + 3\right)}{8}\)
  3. \(y=- \frac{\left(x - 4\right) \left(x + 4\right)}{2}\)
  4. \(y=- \frac{3 \left(x - 5\right) \left(x + 3\right)}{8}\)

##ANSWER1##

##ANSWER2##

##ANSWER3##

##ANSWER4##

Answerlist

  • y=-(x - 2)*(x + 2)/2

  • y=(x - 5)*(x + 3)/8

  • y=-(x - 4)*(x + 4)/2

  • y=-3*(x - 5)*(x + 3)/8

  • y=-(x - 2)*(x + 2)/2

  • y=(x - 5)*(x + 3)/8

  • y=-(x - 4)*(x + 4)/2

  • y=-3*(x - 5)*(x + 3)/8

  • y=-(x - 2)*(x + 2)/2

  • y=(x - 5)*(x + 3)/8

  • y=-(x - 4)*(x + 4)/2

  • y=-3*(x - 5)*(x + 3)/8

  • y=-(x - 2)*(x + 2)/2

  • y=(x - 5)*(x + 3)/8

  • y=-(x - 4)*(x + 4)/2

  • y=-3*(x - 5)*(x + 3)/8

Solution

  1. The first graph has roots at -2 and 2. Notice the equation \(- \frac{\left(x - 2\right) \left(x + 2\right)}{2}\) has factors that match those roots. Also, notice the parabola faces downward, and the expression has a negative multiplicative coefficient.
  2. The second graph has roots at 4 and -4. Notice the equation \(- \frac{\left(x - 4\right) \left(x + 4\right)}{2}\) has factors that match those roots. Also, notice the parabola faces downward, and the expression has a negative multiplicative coefficient.
  3. The third graph has roots at 5 and -3. Notice the equation \(- \frac{3 \left(x - 5\right) \left(x + 3\right)}{8}\) has factors that match those roots. Also, notice the parabola faces downward, and the expression has a negative multiplicative coefficient.
  4. The fourth graph has roots at -3 and 5. Notice the equation \(\frac{\left(x - 5\right) \left(x + 3\right)}{8}\) has factors that match those roots. Also, notice the parabola faces upward, and the expression has a positive multiplicative coefficient.
